‚Äñ where $‚Ñì_{jk} = x_{jk}/x_{kk}$ for $k < j ‚â§ m$. ‚¶â

¬ß Properties ‚¶â
¬∂ ‚¶ä
  ‚Äñ The two important properties of the $L_i$ is that they have
    simple inverses and a simple product. ‚¶â

  ‚Äñ Define
    ‚óá ‚¶ä
      ‚Äñ ‚Ñì_k = (0,¬∑s, 0,‚Ñì_{k+1,k}, ¬∑s, ‚Ñì_{m,k}) ‚¶â
    ‚¶â
    so that $L_k = L_k - ‚Ñì_k\transpose{e}_k$ where $(e_k)_i$ is
    1 if $k = i$ and 0 otherwise. ‚¶â
‚¶â

<statement type='proposition'>
  ‚Äñ $\inv{L}_i$ is $L_i$ with the subdiagonal entries negated. ‚¶â
  <proof>
    ‚Äñ From the sparsity pattern of $‚Ñì_k$, we have $e_k^\tp ‚Ñì_k
      = 0$. ‚¶â

    ‚Äñ So
      ‚óá ‚¶ä
        ‚Äñ (I - ‚Ñì_k e_k^\tp)(I + ‚Ñì_k e_k^\tp) = I -
          ‚Ñì_ke^\tp_k‚Ñì_ke^\tp_k = I. ‚¶â
      ‚¶â‚¶â
  </proof>
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ¬∂ ‚¶ä
    ‚Äñ $\inv{L}_{k}‚ààv{L}_{k+1}$ is the unit lower-triangular matrix
      with the entries of both $‚ààv{L}_k$ and $‚ààv{L}_{k+1}$ in
      their usual places. ‚¶â
    <proof>
      ‚Äñ From the sparsity pattern of $‚Ñì_{k+1}$ we have $e_k^\tp
        ‚Ñì_{k+1} = 0$ so that
        ‚óá ‚¶ä
          ‚Äñ \inv{L}_k ‚ààv{L}_{k+1} = (I + ‚Ñì_ke^\tp_{k})(I +
            ‚Ñì_{k+1}e^\tp_{k+1}) = I + ‚Ñì_ke^*_k + ‚Ñì_{k+1}e^*_{k+1}. ‚¶â
        ‚¶â‚¶â
    </proof>
  ‚¶â
</statement>

