¬∂ ‚¶ä
  ‚Äñ If we define $L = L_{1}^{-1} ‚ãØ L_{m-1}^{-1}$ we obtain $A
    = LU$. ‚¶â

  ‚Äñ In other words, we have a factorization (the ‚ù¨ordinary
    reducer factorization‚ù≠) of $A$ in terms of two matrices. ‚¶â

  ‚Äñ The first, $L$ is unit lower triangular. ‚¶â

  ‚Äñ The second, $U$, is upper triangular. ‚¶â
